Plus that is not counting the 60 billion already signed off to the military from the get go.<br>
i am all for having our soldiers getting every damn piece of equipment that they need and assured its the best possible standards of manufacture.<br>
So why is it that we don't have enough apaches to ride shotgun in quadrants to protect them? That would have been first on my order list.<br>
Totally we're looking at about 120 billion for the military from the start to date. 20 billion or so is going for the training of new police. Plus a few odds and ends.<br>
The company Dick Cheney sits as head of board, has affiliates doing all sorts of things in Iraq, from capping wells to feeding US troops. That makes me uncomfortable as he let that happen and did not feel like it would even be perceived as something nefarious.<br>
What has ale burton come away with so far from our Iraq war? See how much we have already spent, and see how much that particular company has brought home. The numbers are very close, that makes me uncomfortable. 67 billion to HB's 60 billion<br>
Unfortunately i feel like there are scandals being swept under the rug. Dick Cheney's secret energy policies and GW's sheer idiotness. Is it any wonder that gw comes from a banking fortune family?<br>
<br>
If the fact that influxing money into the economy works so well to raise the economy were true. Then why should'nt the minimum wage be raised to a living wage?<br>
Funny how conservatives love to talk about tax relief and trickle down, but balk when a living wage is presented. Its really the same thing, except that a higher base standard would actually put the money in the hands of people who would spend it.<br>
<br>
Take Rhode Island, put guards and checkpoints throught and around. Take away every Bess Eaton and D'n Dnts.<br>
Make it impossible for them to work. See what the next generation of them will be doing. Sitting on thier ass and dreaming up ways to cause trouble.<br>
and thus the situation continues.<br>
<br>
i think that the targetting of Hamas leaders actually spurred the last peace deal. It actually works, its funny how these guys can wire someone up and send them to death. Then FReak out when the military targets them.<br>
Until Isreal stfu and the PLO starts arresting terrorists nothing will get done. Right now the terrorists give interviews in hospitals after failed attacks, shouldn't thier government arrest them? hell yeah, unless they are suported by the government.<br>
<br>
if only Rabin were alive, and Abbas got some support, imagine if they could have shaped this situation.<br>
<br>
The real question? Will rebuilding Iraq turn into the friendly democratic dream we have? Or the dream they have. Will the influence from a new Iraq be a beacon of light to tree huggers? Or the power needed to put a nuclear challenge in the middle of a powder keg.<br>
<br>
