That's the problem.  They have a lot to lose.<br>
<br>
If they weren't engaging in terrorist activities, there would be enormous pressure from the rest of the world for the Israelis to compromise and make peace.  As it is, the Palestinians have forced sympathies to the side of the Israelis.  Whether or not you think all is fair in war, the vast majority of the world condemns attacks against civilians without military objectives, and it has an enormous effect on the sympathies of the rest of the world.<br>
<br>
Even without pressure from the rest of the world, Israel has expressed a desire to negotiate with the Palestinians, but not with terrorists or any regime supporting terror.<br>
<br>
Terrorism, rather than helping their cause, is hurting it.<br>
